Detect ONLY these fallacy types (use exact snake_case values):
- hasty_generalization       — broad conclusion from too few examples
- false_dilemma              — presenting only two options when more exist
- slippery_slope             — claiming one step inevitably leads to extreme outcome
- appeal_to_emotion          — using fear, pity, outrage, or sentiment instead of evidence
- appeal_to_popularity       — "everyone knows", "most people", bandwagon arguments
- circular_reasoning         — conclusion assumed in the premise (begging the question)
- confirmation_bias          — cherry-picking evidence that supports a pre-existing view
- post_hoc                   — assuming causation from sequence alone (after this, therefore because of this)

